Package: cgrc.bayes
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian Implementation of the Correct Guess Rate Curve
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("CGRC", "contributors", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "noreply@example.com")
Description: A reproduction of the Correct Guess Rate Curve (CGRC) method of
    Szigeti et al. (2023) and an alternative implementation that expresses the
    uncertainty around the CGR-adjusted treatment effect as a posterior
    distribution rather than through resampling. Provides the four-stratum
    estimand, a Normal-Inverse-Gamma conjugate posterior, a corrected JAGS
    backend and a backend-agreement check, a faithful port of the original
    kernel-density resampling procedure, the activated-expectancy-bias
    generative model with a repeated-simulation operating-characteristics
    study, a region-of-practical-equivalence decomposition, and the
    reference-line diagnostic. The estimand is unchanged throughout; this is a
    different way of computing uncertainty around the published quantity, not a
    different quantity.
